===Etymology===
Partly from {{der|en|fro|comete}} ({{cog|fr|comète}}), and partly from {{der|en|ang|cometa}}, both from {{der|en|la|cometes}}, from {{der|en|grc|κομήτης||longhaired}}, referring to the tail of a comet, from {{m|grc|κόμη||hair}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{enPR|kŏm'ət}}, {{IPA|/ˈkɒmət/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|en-us-comet.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}
* {{rhymes|ɒmɪt|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{lb|en|astronomy}} A [[celestial body]] consisting mainly of [[ice]], [[dust]] and [[gas]] in a (usually very [[eccentric]]) [[orbit]] around the [[Sun]] and having a "tail" of matter blown back from it by the [[solar wind]] as it approaches the Sun.
# A [[celestial]] [[phenomenon]] with the appearance given by the [[orbiting]] celestial [[body]].
# Any of several species of [[hummingbird]] found in the [[Andes]].

